This review and images are based on orders from 2 different days. Some of the reviews I read of this restaurant almost diverted me from placing my first order, but Im glad I didn't bc their baleadas and pupusas are awesome. Yes, there will be a wait on orders you place for pick-up or delivery, especially on busy days/times (think Fridays & Saturdays). My first order was placed for a Saturday night's dinner, I asked how long the wait would be and the person who took my order had an accurate estimate of the waiting period. The wait was a long but I agreed to it, he was efficient and straightforward.  From what I've tried-Baleadas sencillas are great. Pupusas de queso y mixtas, are also great. Pollo con tajadas; I appreciated to be asked if I wanted my tajadas thick or thin, that was unexpected, specially after reading a handful of reviews about their customer service. The chicken thigh was juicy, however, the chicken leg was slightly undercooked, enough for me to not finish eating it. If you are a manager/owner reading this, a meat thermometer can easily prevent this from happening, losing customers and more importantly avoiding food poisoning! -☆  Over the phone and in person two different people took my orders, both were placed with no trouble, except for meeting the minimum requirement for delivery, I live a bit far but once I increased my total they were kind to deliver. Will give the pollo con tajadas a second try just in case the day I called the restaurant was saturated with orders and will adjust/update rating thereafter.  What I noticed from my second order and what consisted of first visit to the restaurant, everything is made to order, they sale home-cooked style meals, do keep this in mind and order before getting hAngry. I wanted to make sure I included this in my review bc some people seem to be expecting fast food from here and many have left harsh comments as if the pandemic hasn't taught many of us to be kind-er, people are making your meals in a kitchen not machines at a food factory.

I am updating the review. Today was my mother's birthday & she wanted an authentic Honduran meal. It was a horrible experience. I told them that I would have a party of four to five people, they put out a table on the sidewalk that only two people can sit but they put four chairs not enough to hold the plates & the drinks. We were surrounded by dirty orange Con-Ed Street cones. There were no gates, no partitions, no fenced off area and no covering or umbrella. Very uncomfortable, the waitress was borderline obnoxious, my mother tried to start a small talk conversation and the waitress quickly ignored my mom and then walked away with no expression on her face. There were no other customers in this place . When she came to get our orders she listened to me and my mom & she ignore the rest of my family. We thought everything was okay, after receiving both my meal and my mom's meal we waited 45 minutes and then said hey what happened to the two orders of  hamburgers. She brought out the the chips in guacamole that was ordered with the hamburgers but she didn't bring the hamburgers out and what did the waitress do instead of apologizing for her mistake? She accuses us and says we didn't order it.  I just looked at her, you think we would order two meals and ignore the other two family members and they just watch us eat, really? She was being very mean and ruining my mom's birthday, afterwards she begrudgingly said we can make the hamburgers if you want. My sons were annoyed and at that point very unhappy with her, she did nothing to make up for it, nothing at all, horrible experience. The boys ended up eating nothing at the restaurant, because the waitress failed to do her job. I still tipped her but maybe I shouldn't have. Was trying to teach my kids to always be fair and tip working people but in the end I don't think this waitress deserved it. She gave the restaurant a bad name, it is her actions that will prevent me from ever coming back to this place and I will tell my family and friends not to come eat here. They have just lost quite a bit of business, if anybody cares, you should not go here to eat. Find a better place that respects the customer and give you a better experience.

It takes a while to get the order out when you dine in but it's only because the food is super fresh. Everything on the menu is made per order, right down to the rice. If you grab a few coronas and chit chat with company the time breezes by. It's well worth the wait when you know the food is clean, authentic, fresh and delicious. Portions are large and can easily be split between 2 people. It's hard to find authentic Honduran restaurants that don't incorporate other central and south American dishes but this place stays true to the roots.

If you are looking for authentic Honduran food in Brooklyn then you have found it here! Restaurant is clean and the food is delicious. The food is made fresh so it may take a bit of time to serve. There's on street parking as well as metered parking.
